Moved MacVim project to src/MacVim and removed runtime folder

Teach git to ignore generated files.Adds entries to .gitignore for all the stuff that gets generated during an ordinary build of MacVim. Also, some automatically-generated files seem to have crept into the upstream repository, so let's remove them.nnSigned-off-by: Tim Allen <screwtape@froup.com>n
Remove MacVim.xcodeproj/winckler.* from repo and ignore src/TAGS

Only update menu state on actual state change.Problem: Menu updates caused noticable delays because every menu item gotnupdated on state changes.nSolution: Remember old state and only pass update event on to MacVim if the newnstate differs from the old one.nnAlso add .*.swp to .gitignore to ignore Vim swapfiles.n

Fix a text rending problem caused by MMTypesetter class in LeopardIn Leopard, Cocoa Text System seems need a concrete instance ofnNSTypesetter for NSLayoutManager, like NSATSTypesetter, otherwise,nthe call to -layoutParagraphAtPoint: simply fails. I guess thatnmethod in NSTypesetter has become virtual in Leopard.n

Fix cursor blinking in insert mode.Calls to draw text with the DRAW_TRANSP flag were ignored.  By not ignoringnthese calls the background of the cursor is erased also in insert mode so thatnblinking works.n
Replace underscores with spaces when parsing font names.Now possible to use eithern  :set gfn=Courier New:h10norn  :set gfn=Courier_New:h10nto set the font.n

Fix :set go+=c and menu autoenabling bugs.Bug: With 'go+=c' Vim could enter a key wait loop while processInput==TRUEnwhich caused all keyboard input to be dropped.nFix: Don't drop keyboard input when processInput==TRUEnnBug: With 'go+c' Vim disabled all menu items before quitting which causednautoenabling not to work so the New Window was sometimes grey when no windowsnwere open.nFix: Enable all menu items in recurseSetAutoenablesItems.n
Reduce update delay when resizing with mouse.By forcing an update of the text view at the end of batch processing of drawncommands the update delay when dragging to resize is reduced.n
Changed DiffText and Constant highlight groups

Add input queue to backend, fixing process leak problem.Mouse and keyboard input is handled immediately, all other input is put on anqueue which is processed whenever gui_mch_update() is called.  This avoids DOncalls to be sent from the backend during processing of another DO call.  (Seencomments in MMBackend processInput:data: and processInputQueue.)  One problemnthis caused was that connectionDidDie notification was not received whennprocessInput:data: got called recursively (and thus processes could leak).nnAlso did some code cleanup to MMBackend.n
Sort .gitignore in alphabetical order for consistencySigned-off-by: Adam Mercer <ramercer@gmail.com>n
Ignore the auto generated file src/auto/if_perl.cSigned-off-by: Adam Mercer <ramercer@gmail.com>n

Draw the current text view size in the titlebar during resize operations.It seems that NSWindows get notfied of each step of the live-resize, butnNSViews get notified of the start and end events. So, we make MMTextViewnforward these notifications to the window controller, and let the windowncontroller figure out when to change the title.nnSigned-off-by: Tim Allen <screwtape@froup.com>n

Ignore DRAW_TRANSP flag.This flag is supposed to indicate that the background should be transparent.nHowever, not setting the background color leads to a rendering artifact wherenthe character after the cursor sometimes is not drawn.  Simply ignoring thenDRAW_TRANSP flag takes care of this bug.n
Use macvim color scheme as default.The color scheme is set in $VIM/gvimrc, but only if the color scheme hasn'tnalready been set (in .vimrc).n

Optimize speed when 'matchparen' is enabled.When matchparen is used gui_mch_update() gets called a lot.  This functionnchecks the run loop for new input which takes a long time.  To speed things upnmake sure that the run loop is only checked every 100 ms or so (controlled bynMMUpdateTimeoutInterval in gui_macvim.m).n
Fix for Leopard Ctl-key bug.In Leopard Ctrl-key events are sent to performKeyEquivalent: instead ofnkeyDown:, so we have to deal with them there as well.n
Vim view refactoring.This fixes the ':set lines=1000000' problem in fu mode.  Furthermore, thisnfixes a regression that the tab sizes weren't adjusted when changing the windownsize.n
New icon set (Gnome/Matt Ball/Jonas Rask derived)
Only respond to left, right and middle mouse clicks.This effectively ignores mouse clicks when [NSEvent buttonNumber] > 2.n
Disable baseline change for underlined text.This fixes a display bug on Leopard where lines with underlined text werenhigher than lines without underlined text.n
Always open a dropped file in new tabAlways use :tab drop when dropping files.  (Used to call :drop when onlynone file was dropped but this would not open the file in a new tab.)n

Launch Vim process via login shell, handle spaces in file namesThe user environment is not always sourced when MacVim starts.  To solve thisneach Vim process is launched via a login shell like this:n$SHELL -l -c exec /path/to/Vim -g <args>nAlso make sure that if an argument contains a space then enclose it in quotes.n

Changed application termination procedureOn applicationShoulTerminate: check the 'documentEdited' flag of each window tondecide whether any buffers were modified instead of making a DO call to eachnVim process.n

Add eval & add input methods to MacVim, apply to file openNow possible to evaluate expressions in a Vim process from MacVim [MMBackendnevaluateExpression:], and to send arbitrary input to Vim [MMVimControllernaddVimInput:].  Expression evaluation is used to query Vim state from withinnMacVim.nnWhen opening a file use these methods to check if it is already loaded, if sonraise the corresponding window (doesn't work for multiple files).n

Don't attempt to open dropped file that is already openWhen a file is dropped, each Vim process is checked to see if the file isnalready open.  If so, raise the corresponding window and select the tab thatnholds the opened file.  Only works when one file is dropped.n

New text drawing model, better unicode support, 'gfw' support, etc.Characters and columns are no longer assumed to be in one-to-onencorrespondence.  Thus when modifying the text storage a (row,column) pair mustnbe searched for.  This is managed usingn[NSString rangeOfComposedCharacterSequenceAtIndex:]nand by marking wide characters with an attribute (called MMWideChar).  Wenalso provide an optimized code path for when characters and columns are innone-to-one correspondence (no wide chars, only chars that can be represented bynone utf16 character).nnA new typesetter is also used.  Instead of overridingnlayoutGlyphsInLayoutManager:::: we override willSetLineFragmentRect::::.  Thisntypesetter can handle composing characters, whereas the old typesetter couldn'tn(it can still be used by setting the user default MMTypesetter tonMMTypesetter2.)nnNote that text rendering still has flaws, the Cocoa Text System and Vim hasndifferent opinions on how much space certain characters take up and thisnresults in display bugs.  (E.g. nonspacing marks such as U+064C arenproblematic.)  Also, sometimes the layout manager hides glyphs but Vim assumesnthat each character is displayed (resulting in yet more display bugs).nnAdded support for 'guifontwide'.  This can be set to anything (different fontnsize); it is quite possible to set it so that the display becomes completelynmessed up.n

Updated help filesUpdated gui_mac.txt to reflect better handling of Unicode.nnNot all occurrences of :action and :menukeyequiv had been changed ton:macaction and :macmenukey.nnUpdated 'guifontwide' entry.n

Support file-open check for multiple filesWhen dropping multiple files, make sure none of the files are already open.  Ifnall files were already open, then select the window and tab of the first filenthat was open.  If at least one file was not already open, then simply ignorenthe open files and open the unopened ones.nnAlso don't check if files exists inside application:openFiles: since files thatnare passed here are assumed to already exists.  The existence check has beennmoved to the system services message openFile:userData:error:.n
Enable trackpad scrolling over the black area in full-screen

Disable login shell with MMLoginShellNew Vim processes are by default launched via a login shell so that the user'snenvironment gets profiled.  This behavior can be disabled by setting the userndefault MMLoginShell to 0.n

Add IM control supportWhen the default system keyboard script is non-roman the input manager isnautomatically switched to a roman keyboard script when going to normal mode.nSee 'imd', 'imc', 'imi' for some relevant options.  MacVim uses annover-the-spot style of IM support.n
Improved marked text handlingDelete, enter, escape, all work as expected with marked text visible.n

Fix autocommands in macvim color schemeCalling ':set bg=dark' in .gvimrc clears colors_name which caused an errornmessage to pop up every time the focus changed due to the autocommandsninstalled in macvim.vim accessing colors_name.n

Preserve swap files after crashBefore terminating gracefully, send a TerminateNowMsgID to every Vim process sonthat they can determine whether MacVim quit or crashed.  If MacVim quits, callngetout() to exit Vim (this removes swap files), otherwise callngetout_preserve_modified() (this preserves swap files).n
MacVim color scheme supports dark backgroundChange background color with :set background=dark (see :h 'background')n
Fix a wide character bugWhen replacing characters in the text storage it could happen that a row 'lost'none column when a wide character was replaced with a normal one.n

Constrain window frame to screen after live resizeAlways send SetTextDimensionsMsgID to Vim at the end of live resize to ensurenthat resizeWindowToFit gets called.  Otherwise the window can be too big andnwill then automatically resize when a dialog sheet is presented or when thenwindow is moved, which feels strange.n
MMLoginShell defaults to NOStarting a tcsh shell with -c and -l doesn't work so disable this user defaultnuntil further notice.n
Improved support for Ctrl-mappingsCtrl-letter keys are passed directly to the input buffer so that the backendncan separate e.g. <C-i> and <C-Tab>.n

ODB Editor protocol (aka 'external editor') supportPrograms that support ODB asks MacVim to open files. When a file is written ornclosed, MacVim notifies the program of these events. (At the moment the 'Burl'nparameter is parsed but ignored. The 'RdEV' parameter is ignored.)n
Docs updated on ODB support, fixed Info.plist
Parse selection range when opening files from XcodeXcode sets the 'keyAEPosition' parameter in the 'odoc' Apple event. Thisncontains information on the line range to select when opening files.n

Add fork supportIf vim is started via '-g', it forks and exec()s a new (!) vim instance in thenchild process. But if the gui is started via `:gui`, no forking is done.nnIn MacVim, pass the '-f' flag when starting a new Vim process (should not forknin this instance).n
Nicer looking tabs on LeopardMake the tabs look almost identical to the Leopard Terminal.app tabs (only onnLeopard, the Tiger tabs are unchanged).n
Cursor line & column darker when bg=dark in macvim color scheme

Fix initial window placementWhen ~/Library/Preferences/org.vim.MacVim.plist does not exist the window willnbe placed according to the frame passed when initializing the NSWindow, so setnsome sane default values.n
Fix tab color flicker problem on Leopard
Fix memory leak in window controllerThe NSWindow object for a window controller was alloc'ed but never releasednwhen initializing the window controller.n
Documentation updatesAdded some info about forking on Mac OS X and some other minor improvements.n
Avoid false 'documented edited' warning when quittingIf a Vim process is quit using :wq the 'document edited' flag is never cleared,nso always clear it during cleanup.n
Update docsFixed typos, updated section on the macvim color scheme as well as the toolbarnsection.n
Fix full-screen mode for secondary monitors

Fixed potential font memory issueThe font was not retained when setting gui.norm_font leading to a pointer intonfreed memory.  The font instance is now retained before its pointer value isnstored in gui.norm_font.n
Experimental ATSUI text rendering supportThe ATSUI renderer can be enabled by setting the user defaultnMMAtsuiRenderer.  At the moment only very basic text drawing is supported.n

Window and view refactoringWindow and view code was refactored to better accomodate the transitionnto the ATSUI text rendering code.  View specific code has beenncompletely moved into MMVimView and window code is now all innMMWindowController; the window controller is also 'full-screen aware'.nFinally, the text storage is no longer referenced outside MMTextView --nthe idea is that the text view is the public class for handling thenwork that MMTextStorage used to be the public interface for.nnThis refactoring also brings some improvements:n- window resizing is more responsiven- full-screen window memory leak fixedn- proper fix for erroneous 'buffer modified' warningn- full-screen no longer tried to set 'nil-title' (this caused backendn  connection problems)n- changing lines/columns in full-screen works properlyn- open dialog now works in full-screen on Tigern
Cursor color change in dark macvim color scheme

Make text view first responder when leaving full-screenThe 'plus' button on the tabline got first responder status when leavingnfull-screen, which (among other things) looks bad when full keyboardnaccess is enabled.nnAlso some code cleanup.n
Ensure menus are updated when window focus changes
Window title is set on both decorated and full-screen window

<M-Up> and <M-Down> not triggered twiceThe default Cocoa key bindings map these key presses to two commandsnwhich led them to be triggered twice.  Avoid this by passingnAlt+Function key presses straight to Vim instead of toninterpretKeyEvents:.n
Removed window nib filesWindows are created programatically instead of via a nib file.n
Give warning if user symlinked to Vim binaryCocoa does not support symlinking because NSBundle then fails to findnresources.  Give a warning if possible symlinking is detected.n

File->Open pops up a modal 'open files' dialogThe File->Open dialog lets the user choose one or more files which arenopened in tabs in a new window; it replaces the behaviour wherenFile->Open presented a sheet which opened (at most) one file in thentopmost window.  This conforms better with the standard File->Opennbehaviour of Mac apps.n

File opening procedure changedWhen files is being opened (via [MMAppControllernapplication:openFiles:]) try to open the files in an untitled windown(either one that is already open, or one that is currently launching).nThis avoids two windows opening when the 'Edit in MacVim' input managernis used, or when files are opened from Xcode.n

Use Launch Services, user default for untitled windowsUse Launch Services when launching MacVim from a Vim process instead ofnusing NSTask.nnAdded user default 'MMUntitledWindow' which controls when an untitlednwindow should open.  It can take the following values:n0 = Never open untitled windown1 = Open untitled window on 'Open' eventn2 = Open untitled window on 'Reopen' eventn3 = Open untitled window on both 'Open' and 'Reopen' eventsn
Added MMTexturedWindow user defaultEnable MMTexturedWindow to get textured window on Tiger (Leopard alwaysnuses a textured window).n
Highlight spotlight queries on openWhen MacVim is started from a spotlight search, the query text fromnspotlight is highlighted.n

Launch MacVim from path instead of bundle idUse bundle path instead of bundle identifier when MacVim is launchednfrom a Vim process.  This avoids problems when there are several copiesnof MacVim.app on the hard drive.n

Revert to using NSTask to launch MacVimUsing Launch Services (LS) caused several problems, so this commitnreverts back to using NSTask to launch MacVim from a Vim process.nnThe most severe problem LS caused was that sometimes MacVim would nevernfinish launching (the dock icon kept bouncing forever).  Rebuilding thenLS database seemed to temporarily fix this problem, but it keptnreoccuring.n
File->Close sends performClose:This fixes a bug where <D-w> would close not close the about dialog box,nbut instead would close a (partially) obscured window.n
Added preference panelThe preference panel is very simplistic at the moment.  We might want tonconsider making it a Safari-style preference panel if the number ofnpreferences increase.n
Warn if multiple tabs or windows are open when quitting
Order window front when opening filesEnsure that the window is ordered front when opening files in an alreadynopen window (otherwise a newly open filed may be in an obscured window).n

Decrease false positives on untitled window detectionThe detection algorithm is still dumb; it now thinks a window isnuntitled (i.e. good for opening new files in) when its title begins withn[No Name] - VIM.  This means that it now rejects modified buffersnwhich haven't been saved to a file.n
Always detect ^CSometimes Ctrl-keys are sent to the backend as text instead of as ancommand key, so we must look for ^C in both cases.nnThis fixes a the ^W^C bug (Issue 48).n
Use Cocoa bindings for preferences panel

Sparkle support for automatic updatesWith this commit the versioning scheme of MacVim has also changed;nCFBundleVersion is now a number (indicating the build), andnCFBundleShortVersionString contains the version number (e.g. 7.1).n
Add 'Check for updates' option to preferences
Update Xcode project file- add 'Universal' configuration (builds a universal binary)n- use 'apple-generic' versioning (agvtool)n
Removed stray entry in Info.plist dictionary
Update preferences panelSome esoteric options were removed; added descriptions to some options.n
Add howto comment to appcast file
Don't hide prefs panel on deactivateThe preferences panel no longer hides when MacVim loses focus.  Also,nsome space has been added between buttons in the preferences panel.n

Track pad scrolling is force sensitiveWhen scrolling with the track pad, check the force the user is scrollingnwith and adjust the number of lines scrolled accordingly.  Previouslyneach track pad event scrolled three lines indepent of how forceful thenscroll movement was.n

Vim search patterns are put on the OS X Find PasteboardBy adding search patterns to the Find Pasteboard other apps can accessnVim search patterns.  For example, if the user typesn/neat<CR>nin MacVim and then switches to Safari and hits <D-g>, then Safari willnsearch for the string neat.n

Find Next/Previous and Use Selection for Find menusImplemented Find Next, Find Previous and Use Selection for Findnmenus.  In the process the Edit->Find menu has been restructured.  Tonaccomodate these changes the code changed so that the Find Pasteboard isnupdated also when :set @/ = ... is called (previously the FindnPasteboard was only updated when an actual search was executed).n
Remove plist/dict from registered file typesThe .plist and .dict entries were removed from Info.plist since files ofnthis type may be in binary format.n
Implement bellThe bell uses NSBeep() and can hence be changed in the SystemnPreferences.  Note that the visual bell is not yet implemented.n
Send cursor position on each batch drawThe cursor position is used to set the selected range in the MMTextView.nThis provides some support for voice over (enable with Mac+F5).n
Change LineNr highlight group in macvim color schemeThis color change affects ':set number' when bg=dark.n
Update AppcastReplaced '<' and '>' with '<' and '>' where necessary.n

Fix Find Pasteboard bugsAs a temporary precaution, the Find Pasteboard is not used during a forknsince this caused the entire machine to lock up.nnAlso, only patterns from a search (/ and ?) are added to the pboard; notnpatterns from a substitution (:s).n

Add script that builds a new snapshotThe script make-snapshot.sh will build a new snapshot, then create anfolder on the Desktop containingnMacVim.appnREADME-snapshot.txtnmvimnThe folder is then archived and compressed (to a file on the Desktop).n
Add info concerning find to MacVim help
Snapshot 22The 'make-snapshot.sh' script has also been updated.n
Cursor drawing and inset support for ATSUI renderer
No CF calls between fork() and exec()Ensure no CoreFoundation calls are made between fork() and exec()notherwise Mac OS X may crash and burn.n
Add MMZoomBoth user defaultIf MMZoomBoth user default is enabled, then the green zoom button willnmaximize horizontally as well as vertically.n
Cmd-click to only maximize vertically when MMZoomBoth is set
Enlarge try/catch block in connect backendThere have been reports of uncaught exception when the backend connects.nHopefully these exceptions will no longer go uncaught.n

Preference panel update, input manager installerThe preference panel now uses Dave Batton's DBPrefsWindowControllernclass.  A (preliminary) Integration panel has also been added whichnadds buttons to install the Edit in ODBEditor input manager, and a waynto choose which editor to use with the input manager.nnThe input manager is now bundled inside MacVim.app and the source codenhas been added to the project.  The original ODB input manager sourcencode was written by Allan Odgaard and was later modified by Chris Eidhofnand Eelco Lempsink to make it work with other editors than TextMate.nnThe installer uses a new AuthorizedShellCommand class.nnDave Batton is credited in the About dialog.n
fileschanged: src/MacVim/AuthorizedShellCommand.h,CAS_DELIMITER,src/MacVim/AuthorizedShellCommand.m,CAS_DELIMITER,src/MacVim/Credits.rtf,CAS_DELIMITER,src/MacVim/DBPrefsWindowController.h,CAS_DELIMITER,src/MacVim/DBPrefsWindowController.m,CAS_DELIMITER,src/MacVim/English.lproj/Preferences.nib/classes.nib,CAS_DELIMITER,src/MacVim/English.lproj/Preferences.nib/info.nib,CAS_DELIMITER,src/MacVim/English.lproj/Preferences.nib/keyedobjects.nib,CAS_DELIMITER,src/MacVim/General.png,CAS_DELIMITER,src/MacVim/Integration.png,CAS_DELIMITER,src/MacVim/MMAppController.m,CAS_DELIMITER,src/MacVim/MMPreferenceController.h,CAS_DELIMITER,src/MacVim/MMPreferenceController.m,CAS_DELIMITER,src/MacVim/MacVim.xcodeproj/project.pbxproj,CAS_DELIMITER,src/MacVim/PSMTabBarControl/PSMTabBarControl.xcodeproj/project.pbxproj,CAS_DELIMITER,src/MacVim/edit-in-odb/Edit in ODBEditor.xcodeproj/project.pbxproj,CAS_DELIMITER,src/MacVim/edit-in-odb/Edit in ODBEditor_Prefix.pch,CAS_DELIMITER,src/MacVim/edit-in-odb/English.lproj/InfoPlist.strings,CAS_DELIMITER,src/MacVim/edit-in-odb/Info,CAS_DELIMITER,src/MacVim/edit-in-odb/Info.plist,CAS_DELIMITER,src/MacVim/edit-in-odb/Makefile,CAS_DELIMITER,src/MacVim/edit-in-odb/src/Edit in ODBEditor.h,CAS_DELIMITER,src/MacVim/edit-in-odb/src/Edit in ODBEditor.mm,CAS_DELIMITER,src/MacVim/edit-in-odb/src/NSTextView: Edit in ODBEditor.mm,CAS_DELIMITER,src/MacVim/edit-in-odb/src/WebView: Edit in ODBEditor.mm,CAS_DELIMITER,src/MacVim/edit-in-odb/url map.plist,CAS_DELIMITER

commit_message: Add Edit in ODBEditor input manager credits
Integration prefs pane update- Make last prefs pane persistentn- Order editor list alphabeticallyn- Set editor on install if it is not setn- Code cleanupn
ODB Input Manager installer is version sensitiveThe Integration prefs pane states which version of the input managerncurrently is installed.  The Input Manager version is bumped from 1.0nto 1.1.n
Update helpAdd comments on automatic updates in important section and MMZoomBothnin hints section.n
Merge upstream Edit in TextMate changes, remove a utf8 char
fileschanged: src/MacVim/edit-in-odb/src/Edit in ODBEditor.h,CAS_DELIMITER,src/MacVim/edit-in-odb/src/Edit in ODBEditor.mm,CAS_DELIMITER,src/MacVim/edit-in-odb/src/NSTextView: Edit in ODBEditor.mm,CAS_DELIMITER,src/MacVim/edit-in-odb/src/WebView: Edit in ODBEditor.mm,CAS_DELIMITER

commit_message: Update the Integration prefs paneThe integration pane now contains descriptive text concerning the 'Editnin ODBEditor' input manager.n
Set <D-C-z> as key equivalent for Window->Zoom menu itemThis key equivalent is the same as in iTunes.n
Integration pane: version label moved, typo fixed

Improved method to start Vim processes in a login shellA login shell is started by exec'ing a shell process whose argv[0] isnprepended with a dash.  Which shell to use can be controlled with userndefault MMLoginShellCommand (or by setting $SHELL).  If the shell needsna parameter to make it a login shell then this can be set with the userndefault MMLoginShellArgument.  The documentation has been updated withnthese new user defaults.n
Higher constrast mouse cursor in insert modeAn Ibeam cursor with a white outline was added to make it easier to spotnwhen 'bg=dark'.n
Add Universal build target to 'Edit in ODBEditor' project
Get rid of compilation warning messages
Line numbers are brighter when bg=darkThis applies to :set number under the macvim color scheme.n
Ensure mouse cursor is setThere is a bug in NSTextView where it keeps resetting the mouse cursornback to the I-beam cursor.  We fix this by setting the custom cursorneach time the mouse moves.n

Fix ODB Input Manager memory issueThe Input Manager failed to retain two string objects which werenaccessed after having been autoreleased.  This patch fixes the bug wherenthe Edit in ... menu entry was corrupted and related issues.nnThe version number of the Input Manager has been bumped to 1.2.n
Take care of compiler warning in MMTextView
Ensure mouse cursor is set (again)The former patch did not work 100% and it also hogged CPU.  This patchnseems to work better and requires no extra CPU.n
Remove build phase from Edit in ODBEditor projectThe removed build phase was a Run Script which called a shell scriptnthat effectively did nothing.n
Update layout of the Integration prefs pane
All prefs panes have same width

Support 'antialias' with ATSUI rendererThis commit adds support for the 'antialias' option with the ATSUInrenderer (the NSTextView renderer still uses System Preferences).  Thendocs on 'antialias' have been updated.nnSome changes to the code used by Carbon Vim is affected by this commit.nA feature flag FEAT_ANTIALIAS was added to support easy disabling ofn'antialias' support.nn(Patch by Jjgod Jiang with some modifications by Bjorn Winckler.)n

Support 'antialias' with default rendererThis provides some support for the 'antialias' option with thenNSTextView renderer.  However, some fonts seem to be unaffected by thisnoption.  In particular, Monaco of point sizes up to 10 always rendernwithout antialiasing.n

Add full-screen optionsWhen entering full-screen the 'fuoptions' option is used to determinenwhether the vim view should maximize in the vertical and/or horizontalndirections.  The previous rows/columns are restored upon returning tonwindowed mode.nnThe help docs for 'fullscreen' have been updated and docs forn'fuoptions' have been added.n

Improve <D-w> behaviourWith this patch <D-w> works as follows:n- if in Ex-mode, exit by sending ^U:vi<CR>n- if the command-line window is open, close it using CTRL-_CTRL-Nn- otherwise go to normal mode and add :q<CR> to the input buffern
Update Help menuAdd MacVim Help item with <D-?> key equivalent, as well as anMacVim Website item which opens up the MacVim website in the user'sndefault browser.n
Disable <D-?> key equivalentThe key equivalent is disabled for now since it only works on Tiger andnnot on Leopard.n
Transparency setting not lost after leaving full-screenFixes bug where setting 'transp' while in full-screen and switching backnto windowed mode would result in the window being opaque.n

Add command line completion to :macaction commandThis enables the user to cycle through all actions by typingn:maca <Tab> and then repeatedly hitting <Tab>.  The help on :maca wasnalso updated.nn(Initial patch by Nico Weber with some changes by Bjorn Winckler.)n

Make copy/paste respect block-wise selectionsWhen text is copied inside Vim we put both the text and the motion typenon the pasteboard.  Text copied from outside Vim never contains thenmotion type so we have to guess between line and character-wise motionntypes in that case.n
Only cascade from windows belonging to Vim processThis ensures that a newly opened window isn't cascaded from e.g. thenpreferences panel.n

Fix initial window placement bugThe algorithm which determines the topmost window only searches throughnvisible windows.  The initial window placement bug was a result of thisnalgorithm returning the (invisible) window whose position was to bendetermined.n
Add 'antialias' to list of non-standard options in help
Cmd-w shows confirmation dialog when buffer modified
Window no longer moves down on zoom

Add Recent Files menuThe recent files menu will only remember files opened from Finder andnnot files opened from within Vim (via :e etc.).  Recent files will alsonbe added to the Recent Items menu under the Apple menu.nn(Patch by Nico Weber with some modifications by Bjorn Winckler.)n
Enable macvim color scheme to work with other Vim ports

Avoid dropping DO message ... warning when quittingThe warning was a result of sending a DO message from Vim and thennimmediately exiting the process.  It is avoided by not sending any DOnmessages while Vim is exiting.n
Add files opened/saved from :browse to Recent Files menu
Snapshot 27The 'make-snapshot.sh' script has been updated to run on Leopard withnPerl support (TCL support is disabled for now).n
Update help which referred to Carbon versionIn particular, state that MacVim does not source $VIMRUNTIME/macmap.vim.n

Change :macmenukey to :macmenuThe new command allows better control over menus with ability to specifynkey equivalent, action, and wheter menu item is an alternate.  These arenspecified as key=value pairs to allow future expansion.  The helpnfiles have also been rewritten to reflect this change.n

Bind File.Close to :conf qWith the introduction of :macmenu it is possible to bind File.Closento :conf q and at the same time have it send the performClose:naction.nnThis patch reverts back to using :conf q since there were problemsnwith File.Close in conjunction with bindings to <C->.n

Add File.Save All menu itemThis patch serves the secondary purpose of showing off the new featurenof being able to specify alternate menu items using the new :macmenuncommand.  When the File menu is revealed either the Save All or thenSave item is displayed, depending on whether Alt is held or not.n
Fix bug in :macmenuMenu item not found lead to bad memory access.n

Coerce MacVim to work with LCCThe LCC (Logitech Control Center) comes with an input manager whichnregisters its own root object with the default NSConnection.  MacVimnuses the root object of the default connection to vend the frontendnobject, so LCC would cause MacVim to never open any new windows.nnTo work around this problem the default connection is no longer used innMacVim, instead a new connection is created and this connection is usednto vend the frontend object instead.n

Improve Edit menu support in dialogsThe Edit menu items cut/copy/paste/select all/undo/redo are wired tonsend the appropriate action messages (now possible with :macmenuncommand) so that they may work with dialogs.  However, to make this workn100%, menus must first autoenable (which they currently do not).  Thisnwill be addressed in a future patch.n

Set 'backspace' in the system vimrcAdd indent,eol,start to the 'backspace' option in $VIM/vimrc to makenthe delete key behave in a more familiar way to new users.  The helpnfile has been update to point out this non-standard behaviour.n

Open and save dialogs track the Vim pwdOpen and save dialogs will open up at the present working directory ofnthe key Vim process.  This can be disabled by setting the user defaultnMMDialogsTrackPwd to 0.  If disabled, these dialogs always open up atnthe last location browsed to (which is the default OS X behaviour).n
Patch a memory leakThe 'vimState' instance variable in MMVimController is now released onndealloc.n
Insert mode cursor respects 'rightleft' optionWhen 'rl' is enabled the insert mode cursor is drawn on the right-handnside of a cell.n
Use menu descriptors instead of tags to locate menu items
Use -[NSApp setMainMenu:] to update main menu
Change heuristic for finding Services menu
Use default menu when no window open, fix 'Recent Files' menu
Add standard menus to default main menu
Hook up MacVim Help on default main menu
Add Cycle Through Windows to Windows menu (remove <D-`> hack)
Add Minimize All and Zoom All items to Windows menu
Default menu MacVim Help item opens help window maximized
Set windows menu even if it is nil

Pass key equivalents to default main menu after main menuThis is so that the key equivalents set up in the default main menu willnwork even when the system gvimrc files hasn't been sourced.  This isnuseful e.g. when -u NONE -U NONE is passed as arguments resulting innthe default Vim menus being used.n
Ignore Recent Files when no File menu is found

Add Cycle Through Windows to default Windows menuThis ensures that Cmd-` works for all windows.  Also changed itsnalternate to read Cycle Backwards Through Windows.  Note that thendefault Windows menu does not contain the alternate since InterfacenBuilder turned Cmd-Shift-` into Cmd-~ which is no longer a validnalternate.n
Validate performClose: in MMWindow and MMFullscreenWindowFailing to validate would cause the Close menu item to be disabled innfull-screen.n
Do not set key equivalent when 'mac_key == 0'

Don't draw control chars in MMTextStorageIt can happen that MMTextStorage is asked to draw characters from thenControl Characters set (e.g. when :shell is invoked).  This wouldncause internal errors in MMTextStorage so when control chars arendetected, simply draw blanks instead.n
Edit->Font->Bigger/Smaller validates properlyFixes bug where the above items were enabled even when all windows werenminimized.n

Ensure Services menu is empty when creating new main menuMMVimController uses a copy of the MacVim menu that is defined insidenMainMenu.nib instead of getting it from the default main menu.  Thisnensures that the Services menu is initially empty for each newnMMVimController.  Without this the setKeyEquivalent: call would fail ifnthe key equivalent already was in a Services menu item (e.g. <D-F> andn<D-L> would fail).n
Give Vim processes some time to terminate before MacVim doesThis should stop MacVim from beeping when Cmd-q is pressed.n
Set title for separator items to ensure valid descriptors
Don't delay loading Buffers menuThis avoids a flickering menu each time a new editor window is opened.n
Use -[NSScreen visibleFrame] to get full-screen max dimensionsThis fixes a bug where the window dimensions were not restored afternleaving full-screen (with 'maxvert' fu-option set).n
Ensure processCommandQueueDidFinish: gets called if exception is raised

Window cycling hardcoded to keycode 50Window cycling is hardcoded to happen when the Cmd key is pressed withnthe key whose keycode = 50.  Having window cycling in the Window menunmeans that window cycling stops working when the keyboard layout isnchanged.  Thus revert back to the old way of dealing with this since itnseems to work better.n
Force flush output queue before showing dialogThis ensures that the swap file information is displayed when the 'swapnfile exists' dialog is shown.n
Force flush output queue before presenting any dialogThe previous commit did not ensure the output queue was flushed beforenbrowse dialogs were shown.n

Dialog box handling updatedKeep waiting for dialog reply until it is received.  Any input receivednduring this wait is discarded unless it is a 'set text dimensions'nmessage (or keyboard/mouse input).  Also, make setDialogReturn: ansynchronous call so that it is less likely to get dropped.n
Set mouse cursor on mouseMoved:This seems to be the only way to get the mouse cursor not to be changednto an I-beam cursor all the time.n

Disable default main menu key equivalent hackIn performKeyEquivalent: do not pass the key equivalent tondefaultMainMenu since this breaks the menus on OS X 10.4.  Also, thisnhack is not strictly needed now that window cycling is hardcoded (and anNew Window menu is always available on the dock menu) so it is just asnwell that it is removed.n

Toolbar buttons respond to mouse clicks againToolbar items send vimToolbarItemAction: instead of vimMenuItemAction:.nThis enables us to separate toolbar items from menu items and can buildnproper descriptors (starting with ToolBar).n

Flush output queue even when 'exiting' flag is setThere are legitimate instances when the queue should flush even thoughnVim is exiting, e.g. to display a 'confirm quit' dialog with 'go+=c'.nnThis patch has the negative side-effect that the dropping DO messagenwarning may occur more frequently.  Another fix for this problem has tonbe devised.n
Never translate Ctrl-click if Alt, Shift, or Cmd are pressed

Guard against reentrant calls to processCommandQueue:If processCommandQueue: is called when inProcessCommandQueue is set wenadd the input to a receive queue and return.  This is to ensure thatnprocessCommandQueue: can only be called once at a time.  Reentrantncalls can be caused by calling a synchronous DO message or by entering anmodal loop in the frontend.n

Ensure vim controllers are released in default run loop modeVim controllers are released when NSConnectionDidDieNotification isnreceived.  This notification can arrive in pretty much any run loop modenso we take care not to act on it until the run loop mode is back tondefault.  Otherwise we run the risk of releasing objects which Cocoa isncurrently using (e.g. view items) and this leads to crashes.n
Fall back on latin-1 if Vim strings are not valid utf-8

Delay processing unsafe command queue itemsUnsafe messages are defined in isUnsafeMessage().  If a message isnunsafe it should only be handled in the default run loop mode.  This isne.g. to avoid deleting Cocoa objects when a Cocoa message may be busynprocessing it (which may happen due to the nature of distributed objectsnand the fact that we process DO message in 'event tracking' mode).n
Delay display of popup menuThe popup menu enters a modal loop so it is not displayed immediately tonavoid blocking inside processCommandQueue:.n
Don't respond to SetWindowTitleMsgID message in live resizeResponding to these messages would clobber the text dimension title thatnis set during live resize.n
Fix typo in Appcast for snapshot 32
Add show hidden files checkbox to open file dialog

Add file for misc code in frontendThe files Miscellaneous.[m|h] should be used for code common to thenfrontend only (code shared with backend belongs in MacVim.[h|m]).  Somencode has been moved from MacVim.[h|m] and some from other frontendnsource files.nnSome code from the previous commit has also been restructured.n
Cmd-? brings up Help menu on Leopard (shows help on Tiger)
Dialogs are always displayed in the default run loop mode
Only show proxy icon if file being edited exists
Add support for a global Plug-In menu

Basic plugin architectureSupports automatic loading of plugins.  Plugins can: add GUI panelsn(which appear in a drawer for now), add global menu items, executenarbitrary Vim script inside its associated Vim instance.nnAlso add routines to evaluate expressions in Vim and automaticallynconvert returned value to a Cocoa object.n
Marked text baseline adjusts for 'linespace' and font baseline
Cmd-=/- work againA category on NSNumber which is essential for Cmd-=/- got lost in thencreation of Miscellaneous.h, so revive this category.n
Fix display issue with marked text at the edge of a window
Draw marked text at pre-edit position
Send print jobs to Preview.appThere are two drawbacks to this method:n1. the temporary file generated by :hardcopy is not deletedn2. Preview shows a save changes? sheet upon closingn
Add menu item to toggle the plugin view drawerThe setting is remembered, so if the drawer was last toggled closed thennit should not open again until toggled.n
Add versioning to the plugin architectureThe plugin architecture version can be retrieved by a plugin from thenapp mediator by calling the majorVersion and minorVersion methods.n
Fix typo in selector name for delayed dialog
Update doc and short version string for Vim 7.2b
Turn off ligatures by defaultTurn off all common ligatures (fi, ffi) and rare ligatures (ct, ss).n
Ensure valid scroll region when deleting/inserting rows
A few MMAtsuiTextView rendering fixes1. Fix AtsuiTextView italic angle problem.n2. Add underline/undercurl support for text drawing.n3. Use default background color to fill the inset area.n

More file opening options (plus quickstart feature)The preferences panel allow for more ways to open files from othernapplications.  This is controlled by three user preferences:n  - MMOpenInCurrentWindown  - MMOpenLayoutn  - MMVerticalSplitnThese options are also respected when dropping files on a window.nnThe quickstart feature is currently disabled by default and can benenabled by setting the user default MMPreloadCacheSize to a positiveninteger.  With it enabled, new windows open more or lessninstantaneously.n
Modify how and when preloaded windows openThis hopefully fixes the bug where a preloaded window sometimes failednto ever show up but MacVim would still think that it was showing.n
Rebuild cache when vimrc/gvimrc files have been modified
Add Advanced preferences paneThe Advanced pane can be used to control the preload cache size.n
New Window item on Dock menu activates MacVim

Current directory handling changesNew processes default to using the user's home directory as the currentndirectory.  When opening files opened from Finder the current directorynis changed to that of the first file opened.n
Change untitled window detection heuristicAlso change terminology to unused editor instead of untitled windownsince the detction has nothing to do with the window's title.n

Change pwd if file is opening in an unused editorWhen opening a file from Finder, set the pwd to the directory the filenresides in but only if the editor window is unused (e.g. it doesn'tnalready have files open in it).n
Missing toolbar icon fallback code fix
Enable cross compilation in Xcode projectDeployment target is OS X 10.4, development SDK is current OS version.n
Use FS Streams to watch modifications in ~/.vim
Smaller FS event latency, cancel previous requests on FS event
Start and stop FS events if needed when preload cache size changes
Clear preload cache on login shell option changes
Change Quickstart slider to checkbox in advanced prefs

Remove duplicate code in text renderersMost of the code shared between the text renderers now resides in anhelper object.  This way it will be a lot easier to maintain severalnrenderers at once.nnAs an added bonus, the ATSUI renderer now has mouse support as well asndrag-n-drop support.n
Add ATSUI renderer option to advanced prefs
Fix compilation problems on OS X 10.4

Fix rounding problem in ATSUI rendererThis problem will cause characters with descender (like 'g')nto be drawn a little bit lower than the correct place. Thusnwill result some extra pixels after the line is cleared.n

Fix Leopard pty problemsProblem: Pseudo TTYs (ptys) are not successfully allocated on Leopardn (or when Vim is compiled on Leopard).nSolution: Do not attempt to use SVR4-compatible ptys on Mac OS X evenn  though configure may detect their presence.n

Avoid dropping incoming DO message ... being loggedThese warnings were caused by a Vim process sending a DO message andnthen immediately exiting so that the process would some times die beforenthe message was received by MacVim.n
Use bundle path for main connection nameThis is to make it easier to run two different versions of MacVimnsimultaneously.n
Insert Vim state message first on output queue when flushing
Release text storage only if text view class is MMTextView
Paragraph tidy up in gui_mac.txt * Some paragraphs weren't formatted properly for the correct linen   length.n * Fixed a small spelling mistake (know -> known).n
Limit scroll wheel message frequencyThis avoids clogging up the DO messaging system on fast machines withnhigh resolution scroll wheels (or track pads).n
About dialog box shows Custom Version
Reorder preferences panelUse login shell is now enabled by default and has been moved to thenAdvanced pane.  Also, when clicking this or the Use ATSUI renderernbutton the preload cache is rebuilt.n
Add support for mvim:// URL handler

Now works to use :maca on VimLeave auto commandTo fix this the output queue is flushed before exiting a Vim process.nAlso, the CloseWindowMsgID is added to the unsafe list so that othernunsafe messages (such as ExecuteActionMsgID) are not delayed until afternCloseWindowMsgID.n

Sort files opened from FinderFinder does not take into consideration the order in which files arenselected anyway, so sorting the files makes opening multiple files morenpredictable without breaking anything.n

Try to ensure new windows open with bottom edge visible on screenIn particular, if new windows are set to open maximized in the verticalndirection then the top of newly opened windows will be in line with thentop of the frontmost window.n
Add option to hide MacVim when last window closes
Add line and column support to mvim:// URL handler

Make Save changes dialog conform to Apple HIGIf 'guioptions' has c set then the standard Vim dialog is usedninstead.nnThe dialog for multiple unsaved changes has also been updated to be anlittle more like the Save changes dialog.n
Update help on mvim:// URL handler

Fix problems with 'fullscreen' and :mksessionIf 'fullscreen', 'lines' and 'columns' are all set in the same Vimnscript then it used to be possible that the latter two options gotnignored.  This would in particular cause problems with :mks.n

Ensure order of files to open is not affected by 'suffixes'Opening the same set of files in a new window and in an already opennwindow could result in the order of the files being different due to annon-empty 'suffixes' option.  This patch clears 'suffix' before openingnmultiple files and restores it afterwards.n
Cmd-E copies selection to Find pasteboard but does not search
Fix blurry text problem in full screen mode for ATSUI
Don't init backend if Vim is about to forkThis way we avoid doing the initializations twice and cut down a bit onnthe startup time when starting MacVim from Terminal.n

Do not allow input queue to fill upThe backend keeps at most one copy of each message on the input queue.nThis makes MacVim feel a lot more responsive e.g. when scrolling thenscreen.  It used to be that holding down 'j' to scroll and thennreleasing 'j' would cause the screen to keep scrolling for a while evennafter the release.n

Be more conservative about flushing output queueDon't flush on gui_mch_flush(); instead only flush when forced (happensne.g. if Vim is about to take a nap) or just before waiting for newninput.  This reduces screen flicker dramatically in certain cases.n

Ignore gui_mch_update()By making gui_mch_update() a no-op the frame-rate is dramaticallynincreased in certain situations.  The downside is that it is no longernpossible to interrupt Vim with Ctrl-C when it is busy processing.n
Check for Ctrl-C when gui_mch_update() is calledSince gui_mch_update() is called so frequently we only check forninterrupts at most once per second.n
Decrease connection polling interval on startupThis reduces the startup time by almost 1 second when starting MacVimnfrom Terminal.n

Cmd-. sends interruptIn other words, Cmd-. is synonymous with Ctrl-C.  The former is standardnfor Mac apps whereas the latter is standard for Vim.  Incidentally,nCmd-. may thus be used as a substitute for Esc to exit insert mode.n

Add New Document Here ServiceThe New Document Here service will create a blank document in thencurrently selected directory.  If new files are set to open in thencurrent window, then the blank document opens in a new tab in thentopmost window, otherwise a new window is opened.n
Simplify Services menuAll services open a new window by default, unless new files are set tonopen in the current window in the General preference pane.n
Fix scrolling bugScrolling now works e.g. after pressing 'f' in normal mode (previouslynthe scrollbar moved, but the window content did not scroll).n
Update fullscreen background color immediatelyIt is no longer necessary to exit and re-enter fullscreen to see changesnto the background setting in 'fopt'.n

Don't coalesce scroll wheel eventsSince the backend now pops off all input events at once whenever itntends to the run-loop, it is no longer necessary to coalesce scrollnwheel events.  In fact, without coalescing the scroll wheel (or tracknpad) feels a lot smoother.n

Put cursor back on cmdline after Cmd-=Changing the font size up/down while the cursor was on the command linenwould cause the cursor to jump away from the cmdline.  This is no longernthe case.  Also fixes a similar problem when showing/hiding the toolbarnby clicking the pill button.n
Add IM support to ATSUI rendererMore functionality now shared between ATSUI and Cocoa renderers.n(Some modifications by Bjorn Winckler.)n
Add keyboard shortcuts to help file

Don't drop non-repeating keyboard inputKeyboard input is not dropped, unless the input was received due to ankey being automatically repeated (as a consequence of the key being heldndown).  This way characters are never dropped while typing, but it alsonavoids situations where the screen doesn't stop scrolling immediatelynwhen j is released after being held.n
Added tool tips for tabs when tab labels are truncated
Added dragging to tab barDragging a file to a tab will open it in that tab.nDragging files to the end of the tab bar will open them in new tabs.n

Modifier key sends EscAdds possibility to make the left Ctrl, Alt, or Cmd key function as ansecond Esc key.  The key will still function as a modifier if held downnin conjunction with another key.  Enable by setting the user defaultnMMFakeEscModifier to:n1 = Left Ctrln2 = Left Altn3 = Left Cmdnany other number disables this functionalitynnBy remapping Caps-Lock to one of the above modifier keys this enablesnthe use of Caps-Lock as a second (and easy to reach) Esc key.  Caps-Lockncan be remapped inside System Preferences -> Keyboard & Mouse ->nModifier Keys....nnThe Esc event is sent when the modifier key is released.  If the key isnnot released within a predefined timeout, then no Esc event isngenerated.  The timeout can be changed by setting the user defaultnMMFakeEscTimeout (a float, specifying the timeout in seconds).nnThe fact that the Esc event is sent on release makes it feel somewhatnsluggish.  It is possible to have the event sent when the modifier keynis pressed by setting the user default MMFakeEscOnKeyDown but then thenleft modifier key can only be used as an Esc key.n
Add preference to change fake Esc modifier key
Add help on modifier key as Esc

Avoid crash when resizing windowSanity check input to gui_macvim_draw_string(); it can happen that 'len'nis non-zero even though first byte of 's' is NUL (test case with filencontaining Chinese characters).n

Use option as meta keyAdded a buffer local option called 'macmeta' which when set causesnMacVim not to interpret option+key presses thus enabling the user tonbind to <M-..>.  Also updated the documentation and added 'macmeta' tonthe .vim syntax file.n
Move window to top of screen if bottom is obscured

Enable basic AppleScript supportPutting this key into the Info.plist file turns on the basic AppleScriptnsupport Cocoa provides.  Doing so allows MacVim to receive some basicnevents.  This gives MacVim a bit better integration into Mac OS X.nnBelow is an example which, when placed in one's .vimrc file,  causes thenwindow to be zoomed during startup.nnlet script='osascript -e tell application MacVim'n. ' -e set zoomed of first window to true'n. ' -e end tell'nau VIMEnter * call system(script)n
Top of window flush with menu bar after zoom

Fix computation of zoomed window frameWhen computing the zoomed window frame ensure that it is constrained tonhold an even number of rows and columns.  This fixes a problem where thenwindow would not un-zoom after being zoomed.n
Delay flushing send queueEnsure that the send queue is flushed after processCommandQueueDidFinishnsince that method may add messages to the send queue.n

Constrain window size during live resizeEnsure that the window size isn't larger than the visible frame of thencurrent screen.  This avoids problems where the window would snap backnimmediately after being resized manually.n

Fix set lines=999 in .gvimrcEnsure that the window fits on screen when the window is resized to fitnthe content.  This should fix a problem where the window would not benflush with the menu bar when set lines=999 was added to .gvimrc.n
Keep whole window visible on :set lines=X columns=Y
Fix Special Characters palette bugIt is again possible to insert text from the Special Charactersnpalette (broken by commit 8fbb13da74a1912839e9302ebc725df67619c9c0).n

Revert Modifier key sends Esc related commitsThis reverts the following three commits:n  3ae360ddb38dd49e9392aad7a70f0f31a30849een  007bb96eb3ec035169510caa4e206ab901e4b6d0n  b6c06f31be1e8124ed12cc2ff5361752df1e4634n
Add help on how to remap Caps Lock to Esc
More help on menu key equivalents

Connection not in event tracking mode by defaultOnly add backend connection to event tracking mode when it is absolutelynneeded.  At the moment this happens when the window is in live resizenor when the mouse button is held on some part of a scroller.n
Add help on symlinks to mvim script

Support mvim script symlinks to [m|g]ex, rmvimSymlinks to mex or gex starts MacVim in ex mode.  Symlinks to exnstarts Vim in ex mode (no GUI).  Symlinks to rmvim (or rgvim whichnwas already supported previous to this patch) starts MacVim innrestricted mode.n

Data received from system services replaces selectionWhen data is received from system services it replaces the currentnselection.  The current implementation is a bit naive in that it assumesnthat Vim is in Visual mode (it doesn't even work in Select mode).  (Tontest this functionality: enter 2+3, select it, then hit Cmd-* and thenselection is replaced with 5.)n
Explicitly ignore SIGCHLD to avoid zombies
Add Reload/Ignore All buttons to file changed dialog
No error message when dropping files (Issue 135)
Use default SIGCHLD handler in Vim processes
Exit if connection becomes invalidThis is only a temporary measure until a proper fix is found.n
Add <D-BS> and <M-BS> insert mode mappingsThese are standard shortcuts in Mac OS X.  <D-BS> deletes a whole line,n<M-BS> deletes the previous word.n

Handle TerminateNow input message immediatelyFixes a bug where code which waits on the run loop fails to detectnTerminateNow input messages (this could e.g. result in a leak of Vimnprocesses when Quickstart was enabled).n
Input Method is disabled by defaultThe IM code is a bit flakey so keep IM disabled by default for now.n
Add clipboard support in non-GUI mode
Fix character escaping for New File Here serviceThis also makes this service work on Tiger.n

Automatically generate document iconsDocument icons are generated using the makeicns program and a Pythonnscript.  Note that the script uses PyObjC and hence requires Mac OS Xn10.5 or later (on earlier systems a blank icon will be used for allndocument types).nnThis patch also adds more filetypes to Info.plist.nnIntegration into Xcode project by Bjorn Wincklern<bjorn.winckler@gmail.com> with the help of Keith Hubbardn<keith@bangj.com>n
Small doc icons look sharper, faster generation
Make icon generation script faster and more flexible
Look for toolbar icons in runtime path
Show dialog when clicking to close modified tab
List all non-standard options and commands in help
Icon generation works on Tiger again
Toggle menu bar on focus change in full-screen
Add user default to toggle the add tab buttonThe user default MMShowAddTabButton controls whether the add tabnbutton is displayed on the tab bar or not.n

Avoid Press ENTER... promptWhen adding input programmatically the 'silent' flag is automaticallynset.  Hopefully this will mean the end of the annoying Press ENTER...nprompt.  This also means that it should no longer be necessary tonmanually try to make commands silent (e.g. :redr|f should not benneeded).n
Deprecate redr|f in addInput: callsThe previous commit ensures these are no longer neeeded (they used to benthere to avoid the Press ENTER... prompt).n
Fix double free memory problemThis bug was introduced in commit:ne162109d6f022942edb7281736f587ee79e20bfen
Build Debug and Release using default SDKThe Universal target still builds using the 10.4u SDK.n
Don't load default font in Vim (faster startup)Loading and unloading a font can take a substantial amount of time sonthis cuts down on the startup time.n

New user default MMLoadDefaultFontWhen enabled the default font is loaded from within the app bundle eachntime MacVim is started (the default setting).  Startup times are shorternif this is disabled.  Note that if the default font has already beenninstalled on the system then this may as well be disabled.n
Clean up process termination codeExiting immediately on TerminateNowMsgID simplifies the code a bit andnalso minimizes the probability of a process not terminating beforenMacVim.n
Make no DO calls during app termination

Don't ignore SIGCHLD (fix automatic updating)Ignoring SIGCHLD caused problems with automatic updating (Sparkle) sincenit uses popen() (and hence implicitly uses wait4()) to unpack archives.nNow that SIGCHLD is no longer ignored we have to reap child processesnafter exiting a Vim process as well as when MacVim is about tonterminate.n

Show output from external commands as it happensPreviously, all output was sent to the frontend at once so only the lastnfew rows were visible.  This was a bit disconcerting when a command tookna bit of time because there was no feedback that anything was happening.nThe downside to this patch is that it takes a bit longer for a commandnto finish since the frontend has to do more drawing.n

Cmd-. sends SIGINTCtrl-C does not always work to interrupt a stuck Vim process. By makingnCmd-. send SIGINT it is more likely to succeed where Ctrl-C has failed.n(E.g. Ctrl-C may fail if a DO message is dropped, or if the Vim processnis stuck in a loop and isn't checking for new input.)n

Prune draw queue before sending to frontendIf the draw queue fills up with lots (i.e. twice the number of max rows)nof insert/delete line commands we can remove draw commands from thenbeginning of the draw queue.  This reduces the possibility of the drawnqueue overflowing.n
Fix typo in debug message string
Opening with search text does inclusive search

Respect layout pref when raising an open fileFor example, with layout set to arglist and with 'hidden' enabled,ndouble-clicking an already open (but hidden) file will no longer causenit to open in a new tab.  Instead it opens as if the :buf command hadnbeen used.n
Always respect MMLayoutVerticalSplitThis flag used to be ignored when dropping a file onto a window.n
Fix two minor memory leaksThe MMTextViewHelper class failed to release two objects on dealloc.n
Remove .pyc files from icons folder on clean
Tell Git to ignore .pyc files in icons folder
Avoid exception in key handling routine

Fix <C-]> on German keyboard layoutInstead of checking for Ctrl-character, check when Cocoa translates ankeypress to an unprintable character (in particular, this happens onnCtrl-character).  This ensures keys like <C-]> work on (some) keyboardsnwhere ] requires the use of Alt.n
Ensure viminfo is written on Cmd-q
Ignore temporary files in src/MacVim/icons folder
Make icon module compilation more portable
Add more files in MacVim/icons to .gitignore

Fix untitled window on reopen bugWhen MacVim is started from Terminal -MMNoWindow yes is passed as annargument.  This argument will no longer stop new windows from opening onnreactivate events -- it only affects activate events.n
Fix untitled window on reopen with quickstartThis reverts commit 662aa32b399c1149daa1cd3a2b5bccc8e75f589a andnclarifies the comment regarding how 'pidArguments' is used.n

Fork directly after command line scanThis fixes a bug with relative paths as arguments when 'autochdir' wasnenabled and also cuts down on startup times.  However, it also has thennegative side-effect that 'f' is no longer supported in 'guioptions'.n
Don't update 'fuoptions' before GUI has startedThis avoids allocating the MMBackend object before forking.n
Revert Don't init backend if Vim is about to forkThis reverts commit ef03c36272e9a45f71659df7cecfce7aa15c2cbf.nnConflicts:nntsrc/MacVim/gui_macvim.mn
Mention that 'go' does not support f in help
Set correct protocol for frontend proxy

Colors.plist autogenerated from showrgb commandThe Colors.plist dictionary is now generated from showrgb to properlynmatch rgb.txt.  Also add three colors which were missing from the outputnof showrgb (darkyellow, lightmagenta, lightred).n
Fix <C-Tab> regressionThis fixes a regression introduced with commmitnc79be7f927aff8b2b52a6d8d917b899154ab0ff9 where Ctrl+Unprintable keynpresses could no longer be mapped to.n
Tab labels only shows file name tail
Revert temp patch, fixed properly in 7.2.121This patch ensures that Ctrl-C works during lengthy :grep operations innGUI mode.n
Fix set go+=rT bugThe number of columns now matches the width of the window after callingnset go+=rT.n
Fix full-screen zooming with Dock visibleThis fixes a bug where 'set fu=maxvert' would not cover the screennvertically if the Dock was visible.n

Validate screen before constraining windowIf a window is on a screen that gets unplugged it may happen thatn[NSWindow screen] returns nil.  Guard against this when constrainingnthe window frame to the screen frame.nnThis fixes a bug where a window could disappear if it was on a screennthat got unplugged.n

Exit full-screen if the window movesThe window is not supposed to move in full-screen mode so if thisnhappens then exit full-screen.  This situation can occur e.g. if thenwindow is on a screen that gets unplugged.n

Do not hide toolbar unless requestedCommit 2d497eabe995ed7f667d67166b396dff6389d12f introduced a regressionnwhere the toolbar automatically hid upon startup regardless whether 'go'nincluded the T flag or not.n
Use guisp color for underline in ATSUI
Avoid forever bouncing dock iconThis problem was caused by calling the Carbon function KeyScript() fromnthe Vim process.n
Vim talks only to app controller- dialog support not implemented yetn- live resizing not supportedn
Guard against re-entrant calls to process input
Clear delayed vim controller calls on cleanup
Deprecate inProcessCommandQueue related codeWe are guarding against re-entrant calls in the app controller now sonthe inProcessCommandQueue related code is now obsolete.n
Do not modify frontend state in DO callsIn particular, delay all state changes that used to be made insidenconnectBackend:pid such add adding vim controllers to the vimControllersnarray.n
Deprecate performSelectorOnMainThread callsUse performSelector:withObject:after:delay instead since itnautomatically only triggers in default mode.n

Avoid enumerating vim controllersDon't enumerate vim controllers when processing input since it maynpotentially be a huge operation.  If the vim controller array were to benmodified during input processing (should never happen) MacVim would crash.n

Fix Quickstart regressionOutput from a Vim process may reach the frontend even if the process isncached.  Thus when processing input queues in the frontend, also checknif the input came from a cached controller else it could be silentlynignored.n
Beware exceptions when processing inputAdded comment on the dangers of exceptions being raised when processingninput in the frontend.  Shuffled the exception handling around in thenvim controller.n
Add function to print message queue
Add show hidden files checkbox to save dialog
Fix compilation problems on TigerThe NSRunLoopCommonModes constant is not defined in the Tiger API sonexplicitly enumerate the necessary modes instead.n
Add markdown as supported file type
Move all IM code into frontend
Add reStructuredText as supported file type
Change name of window menu itemsChange Next/Previous Tab to Select Next/Previous Tab to keep titlesnthe same as in e.g. Safari.n
Support Quick Look for all known file extensions

Normalize filenames to NFKC before openingVim does not cope very well with Unicode decomposed form NFD (i.e. itndoes not normalize to composed form before rendering) which causesnproblems since HFS+ stores filenames in NFD.  To work around this issuennormalize to compatibility form C before passing filenames to Vim.nn(This is not a solution to the problem with NFD since files stored innNFD will still be problematic but at least a user can work around thisnissue by making sure files are in composed form before opening them.)n
More normalization of filenames, use NFCApparently NTFS uses NFC so switch to NFC instead of using NFKC.n

Dialog sheet animation can no longer cause a crashExplicitly force the sheet animation to be performed before passing thenresult of the sheet on to the backend.  Before this patch the animationnwas performed asynchronously and this could lead to a Vim controllernbeing released at the same time as the animation was being performednsince the animation took place in the default run loop mode.n
Add README-repo.txt fileFor the readme section on the repo web page.  Pandoc is used tongenerate the HTML file.n
ATSUI clips text to avoid bleeding
Set right pwd when dropping a folder on Dock iconThe last path component of the folder that was dropped is no longerndisregarded.n

Refactor keyboard input codeThis both cleans up the code as well as improve support for binding tonmore key combinations.  The Cocoa key bindings system is effectivelyndisabled; a custom key binding dictionary is set up in KeyBinding.plistn(so that keyboard navigation works in dialogs).n

Improve IM support for 10.5When using set noimd remember which input source was used in normalnmode separately from the input source used in insert mode.  This way itnis possible to e.g. use a US layout in normal mode and a non-US layoutnin insert mode.nnThe input source used in normal mode must be ASCII capable or it won'tnbe remembered -- any input source used in insert mode is remembered.nnOn 10.4 the IM code is unchanged because 10.4 does not support the TextnInput Source Services.n
Add note on improved IM support to the help
Only set ASCII IM source when setting 'noimd'The layout used in normal mode (IM disabled) no longer changes when IMnis disabled.  It only changes when the 'noimd' option is set.n
Don't remember IM source if ASCIIThis fixes a bug where the IM source would be forgotten whenever commandnline mode was entered (with 'noimd' set).n
Add rudimentary inline IM supportNot possible to move cursor in marked text.n
Add support for +ximInline marked text editing, underline marked text (even on commandnline), etc.n
Add user default MMUseInlineImUse inline IM (Vim draws marked text) when on, use old IM drawing codenotherwise.n
Fix arrow and function key bug on TigerThe bug caused arrow (and function) key presses to be sent twice.n
Fix Ctrl key regressionFix Ctrl-h, Ctrl-@ and Ctrl-o regression.  Also remove all key bindingsninvolving arrays from KeyBinding.dict.n
Fix Cmd key regressionShift and Alt modifiers now register in combination with Cmd and e.g.narrow keys.n

Avoid race condition (e.g. when closing windows)The app may become multithreaded e.g. due to the open panel beingndisplayed.  In this case connectionDidDie notifications may arrivenoutside the main thread, possibly leading to windows being closednsimultaneously on multiple threads.  This scenario could happen e.g.nwhen quitting with multiple windows open.nnTo avoid this situation performSelectorOnMainThread: is used instead ofnperformSelector:.n

IM enhancementsBy the default the keyboard layout matching the current locale is used.nAlso fix bug where IM switching got confused after manually changing thenIM with Cmd-Space.  Finally, fix support for Ctrl-^ when IM is enabledn(e.g. this did not previously work with the Kotoeri input manager).n
Fix window cascadingWindows always cascade a fixed amount down and right from the topmostnwindow.  If the window sticks out on the right/bottom then it is movednas far left/up as possible.n
Disallow comments in :macmenu commandThis is necessary, otherwise e.g. Edit.Paste<Tab>+gP does not parsenproperly.n
Fix handling of built-in toolbar iconsIn particular, this patch ensures that built-in toolbar icons arenproperly used when menus are translated.n
Disable localized menus in system vimrcCan be enabled by setting/clearing 'langmenu' in ~/.vimrc.n
Make Find and Replace dialog localizable
Set $VIM and $VIMRUNTIME earlyOtherwise bindtextdomain() gets the wrong runtime path insideninit_locale() causing messages never to be translated.n
Delete user config files from PSMTabBar project
Build PSMTabBar against current OS version
Ignore user files in PSMTabBar framework
Build Edit in ODBEditor against current OS version
Ignore user files in Edit in ODBEditor framework
Fix warnings in Edit in ODBEditor
Don't use Carbon framework from 10.4u sdk
Copy Sparkle framework into app bundleThe previous commit accidentally removed the step where the Sparklenframework got copied into the app bundle.n
Fix icon generation on Snow LeopardSnow Leopard seems to not support Scrap Manager, so don't use the ScrapnManager code.n
Declare PSMTabBarControl delegate on 10.6This avoids a compilation warning, nothing else.n
Don't use +[NSConnection defaultConnection]The defaultConnection message was deprecated in 10.6.n
Ensure Vim compiles as 32 bitThe MacVim binary always builds as 32 bit so make sure the Vim binary isn32 bit as well (GCC defaults to 64 bit on Leopard).n
Fix some Xcode static analyzer warningsThe only relevant complaint was a memory leak when opening files fromnFinder.n

Disable the ATSUI renderer on 10.6ATSUI has been deprecated on 10.6.  As it stands the ATSUI renderer doesnnot even work and it spews out masses of warnings when building, sonATSUI is disabled when compiling for 10.6 for now.n

Use availability macros correctlyAlways use >= when checking lower bounds and < when checking uppernbounds. The problem is that MAC_OS_X_MAX_ALLOWED andnMAC_OS_X_MIN_REQUIRED need not be equal to one of the MAC_OS_X_VERSION_*nmacros.  For example, on 10.5.8 MAC_OS_X_VERSION_MAX_ALLOWED is 1058nwhereas MAC_OS_X_VERSION_10_5 is 1050.nn(Based on a patch by Michael Guntsche.)n
MAC_OS_X_VERSION_10_6 not defined on pre-10.6Just use a literal 1060 in header files which do not (and should not)ninclude MacVim.h.n
Make Services work on 10.6Services need a (possibly empty) NSRequiredContext dictionary in thenapplication's Info.plist on 10.6.n
Fix New Document Here ServiceExpand leading tilde in paths, else NSFileManager thinks the path doesnnot exists.n
Fix Ctrl-C handlingThis fixes a bug where mappings to e.g. <C-c>g would fail.n
Really fix icon generation on Snow Leopard
Strip x86_64 arch from Ruby LDFLAGS
Don't pass 'long' vars over process boundaryThe only place 'long' was used was in scrollbar identifiers.  These arennow truncated to fit inside 32 bit (when compiling for 64 bit).n
Prepare PSMTabBarControl for 64 bitChange unsigned -> NSUInteger, float -> CGFloat as necessary.n

Disable MacVim plugins for nowThe supporting files for CTGradient and RBSplitView causes severalnwarnings when compiling for 64 bit.  Since nobody uses MacVim pluginsnI have decided to disable them instead of having to support these filesn(although these warnings are easy enough to fix for anybody interested).n
Prepare for 64 bitMostly fixes problems involving NSUInteger.n
Force 32 bit, remove Universal configurationThe Sparkle framework does not include a 64 bit binary, so force 32 bitnuntil it is updated.n
Use MacVim instead of Carbon GUI by default
Add --with-macsdk flag to configureCompilation fails for some reason, so this option is disabled.n
Clean up Carbon includesDon't use FlatCarbon when building MacVim (only for Carbon GUI).n
Fix 64 bit compilation warnings in backend

Strip all -arch flags from Perl and RubyThe system provided Perl and Ruby libraries adds -arch flags since theynwere built as universal binaries.  This causes Vim to build with thesenflags which is undesirable (the default should be to only build for thennative architecture).  The solution is to strip any -arch flags fromnPerl and Ruby.nnA universal binary can be built by using the --with-archs configurenflag.n
Remove unnecessary include paths in Makefile

Deprecate mac-arch, superseded by --with-macarchsMove --with-macarchs and --with-macsdk to an earlier place in thenconfigure script.  The flag --with-macsdk is now enabled but it shouldnalso set the MACOSX_DEPLOYMENT_TARGET environment variable (how?).n
Enable 64 bit compilation (Vim and MacVim)Note that Sparkle currently is not 64 bit so automatic updating won'tnwork when MacVim is compiled for 64 bit.n

Don't include Carbon.h in os_mac.hThis avoid polluting the global namespace with Carbon symbols (there wasna conflict between Carbon and Ruby both defining ID).  To accomodatenthis the Carbon types OSErr and OSType have been changed to int16_t andnuint32_t, respectively.n
Clean Python and Ruby flags when macsdk is setMost importantly there are no explicit -I.. flags that break then--with-macsdk functionality.  Also use -framework Ruby and include Rubynproperly.n
Add missing defines to TigerCGFloat and NS[U]Integer were introduced in 10.5, make sure they arendefined when compiling for 10.4.n
Fix wide character support for 64 bit
Update UTIs in Info.plistIdeally all org.vim.*-file UTIs should be replaced with proper UTIs, butnthey can be hard to find so they will be replaced as new UTIs are found.n
Fix window tiling with multiple monitors
Fix Ruby compilation on case-sensitive FS

Fix full-screen drawing issuesThis commit fixes a problem where the screen would look blurry, or whereneach redraw would cause the entire screen to be cleared before thenredraw (only the Core Text renderer was affected by this bug).n

Avoid forcing redraw in full-screenPreviously the content view in full-screen mode would get redrawnnwhenever the Vim view possibly changed size.  Now the view is onlynupdated if the view did change size (fixes redraw problems with the CorenText renderer).n
Remove SUUpdater object from MainMenu.nibThis avoids an annoying warning on each startup (Sparkle, which thisnobject belongs to, has temporarily been disabled).n

Autosaved dimensions do not override vimrcSetting 'lines' and 'columns' in .vimrc works again.  This patch alsonfixes a minor memory leak related to the autosaved dimensions.  Finally,nskip checking terminal capabilies when the GUI is about to start.n
Update Advanced preferences paneRemove the Use login shell option, and rename the ATSUI option (sincenCore Text may actually be used and not ATSUI).n
Fix transparency for Core Text renderer
Add MMRenderer user defaultSet to 0 for Cocoa renderer, 1 for ATSUI, 2 for Core Text.  The defaultnis 0.n
Avoid 0x0 window when autosaved dimension missingThis fixes a bug where the first window would be tiny if no autosavedndimensions existed on startup.n
Remove MMAtsuiRenderer user defaultThis has been deprecated in favor of MMRenderer.n
Fix ATSUI/Core Text compilation issues on Tiger
Remove references to MMAtsuiRenderer in nib file
Fix Ctrl-Tab handling in Core Text

Improve Find pasteboard interactionPut two representation of the search pattern on the Find pasteboard: onenthat holds the unmodified pattern, and a second one that removes somencommon backslash escapes from the first.  The second pattern will benused by other applications so e.g. hitting * in MacVim and then Cmd+g innanother app now works.n

Use device colors instead of calibrated colorsThis fixes a bug in full-screen where the full-screen background colornin set fuopt=background:Normal would not match the background color ofnthe Vim view (with the experimental renderer).n
Remove config.h from the distribution, let's see if that works.
Add an .hgignore file (suggested by Mike Williams).
Fixed encoding name in Ukranian message file.
updated for version 7.2.328 Problem:has(win64) does not return 1 on 64 bit MS-Windows version. Solution:   Also check for _WIN64 besides WIN64.
updated for version 7.2.329 Problem:g_ doesn't position cursor correctly when in Visual mode and t'selection' is exclusive. (Ben Fritz) Solution:   Call adjust_for_sel().
updated for version 7.2.330 Problem:Tables for Unicode case operators are outdated. Solution:   Add a Vim script for generating the tables.  Include tables for tUnicode 5.2.
Add a few missing runtime files.
updated for version 7.2.331 Problem:Can't interrupt echo list for a very long list. Solution:   Call line_breakcheck() in list_join().
updated for version 7.2.332 Problem:Crash when spell correcting triggers an autocommand that reloads tthe buffer. Solution:   Make a copy of the line to be modified. (Dominique Pelle)
updated for version 7.2.333 Problem:Warnings from static code analysis. Solution:   Small changes to various lines. (Dominique Pelle)

updated for version 7.2.334 Problem:Postponing keys in Netbeans interface does not work properly. Solution:   Store the key string instead of the number.  Avoid an infinite tloop. (Mostly by Xavier de Gaye)
