updated for version 7.2.338 Problem:Part of FD_CLOEXEC change is missing. Solution:   Include source file skipped because of typo.
updated for version 7.2.339 Problem:Part of --startuptime patch is missing. Solution:   Add check for time_fd.
updated for version 7.2.340 Problem:Gcc warning for condition that can never be true. (James Vega) Solution:   Use start_lvl instead flp->lvl.
updated for version 7.2.341 Problem:Popup menu wraps to next line when double-wide character doesn't tfit. (Jiang Ma) Solution:   Display a > instead. (Dominique Pelle)
updated for version 7.2.342 Problem:Popup menu displayed wrong in 'rightleft' mode when there are tmulti-byte characters. Solution:   Adjust the column computations. (Dominique Pelle)
updated for version 7.2.343 Problem:Can't compile on Win32. Solution:   Insert the missing bar.
updated for version 7.2.344 Problem:Can't compile on some systems Solution:   Move the #ifdef outside of the mch_open macro. (Patrick Texier)
updated for version 7.2.345 Problem:Tab line is not updated when the value of 'bt' is changed. Solution:   Call redraw_titles(). (Lech Lorens)
updated for version 7.2.346 Problem:Repeating a command with @: causes a mapping to be applied twice. Solution:   Do not remap characters inserted in the typeahead buffer. (Kana tNatsuno)
updated for version 7.2.347 Problem:Crash when executing <expr> mapping redefines that same mapping. Solution:   Save the values used before evaluating the expression.
updated for version 7.2.348 Problem:Unicode double-width characters are not up-to date. Solution:   Produce the double-width table like the others.
updated for version 7.2.349 Problem:CTRL-W gf doesn't put the new tab in the same place as tab split tand gf. (Tony Mechelynck) Solution:   Store the tab number in cmdmod.tab.

updated for version 7.2.350 Problem:Win32: When changing font the window may jump from the secondary tto the primary screen. (Michael Wookey) Solution:   When the screen position was negative don't correct it to zero.
updated for version 7.2.351 Problem:Can't build with some compilers. Solution:   Move the #ifdef outside of a macro.  Cleanup the code.
Fill the square under the left scrollbarThis fixes a drawing issue that appeared on :vsp.n
updated for version 7.2.352 Problem:Win64: Vim doesn't work when cross-compiled with MingW libraries. Solution:   Always return TRUE for the WM_NCCREATE message. (Andy Kittner)

Fix vert split problems in Core Text rendererThe display is no longer corrupted on :vsp when using the Core Textnrenderer.  Also fixes a problem where background would not be clearedncorrectly when left scrollbar was visible.nnRemove a hack in live resizing code when using CT.  This may cause thenwindow to flicker more during live resize (have to find a better fix).n
updated for version 7.2.353 Problem:No command line completion for :profile. Solution:   Complete the subcommand and file name.

updated for version 7.2.354 Problem:Japanese single-width double-byte characters not handled correctly. Solution:   Put 0x8e in ScreenLines[] and the second byte in ScreenLines2[]. t(partly by Kikuchan)

updated for version 7.2.355 Problem:Computing the cursor column in validate_cursor_col() is wrong when tline numbers are used and 'n' is not in 'cpoptions', causing the tpopup menu to be positioned wrong. Solution:   Correctly use the offset. (partly by Dominique Pelle)

updated for version 7.2.356 Problem:When 'foldmethod' is changed not all folds are closed as expected. Solution:   In foldUpdate() correct the start position and reset fd_flags when tw_foldinvalid is set. (Lech Lorens)
Avoid window flashing white when first shownThis only applies to the Core Text renderer.n
Avoid window flashing white when zoomingThis applies to the Core Text renderer only.nnThere is still a short annoying flash when clicking the zoom button tonmake the window smaller.n
Avoid display corruption on :vsp and 'go' changesAlways redraw the screen when splitting vertically or when the 'go'noption is modified (it may e.g. cause scrollbars to hide/show).n

Backend initiates window zoomingDon't change the window size immediately upon pressing the zoom button.nInstead send the message to Vim and let it resize before the windowndoes.  This avoids flickering problem when zooming with the Core Textnrenderer.nnThe zooming is also slightly smarter about which window size to restorenif the toolbar was hidden while the window was zoomed.n
updated for version 7.2.357 Problem:When changing 'fileformat' from/to mac and there is a CR in the ttext the display is wrong. Solution:   Redraw the text when 'fileformat' is changed. (Ben Schmidt)
updated for version 7.2.358 Problem:Compiler warnings on VMS. (Zoltan Arpadffy) Solution:   Pass array itself instead its address.  Return a value.
updated for version 7.2.359 Problem:Crash when using the Netbeans join command. Solution:   Make sure the ml_flush_line() function is not used recursively. t(Xavier de Gaye)

Place scrollbars correctly for positive insetMake sure that the scrollbar stretches to the top of the window even ifnthe text inset is > 0 (and similarly for the horizontal scrollbar).nThis applies to the Core Text and ATSUI renderers only.n

Allow window resizing across multiple screensIt is now possible to drag to resize a window to be larger than onenscreen.  However, if the window size changes programmatically (due tonscrollbars or toolbar hiding/showing, etc.) then the window will benconstrained to fit on the screen holding most of the window.  This isnperhaps annoying but at least it is consistent with the way Terminal.appnworks (try opening a new tab when a Terminal window spans two screens).n

Alt+Space mappings in Keyboard Layouts now workFor example, French Dvorak assigns Underscore to Alt+Space.  Withoutnthis patch Alt+Space would produce a Space, whereas with this patch itnwill produce an Underscore.n
Add wide font support to Core Text renderer
Fix memory leak in ATSUI rendererThe wide font was not released properly.n
Resize view properly when showing toolbarFixes a bug where the view would not resize when the window covered thenheight of the screen and the toolbar was shown.n

Abandon marked text when switching IMThis fixes a bug with Chinese IM where pressing o in normal mode wouldncause Vim to start a new line and then insert o into the text.  Withnthis patch the o is no longer inserted.n

Update Services for Snow LeopardRename Services so that it is clearer what they do when they appear inncontext menus:nNew MacVim Buffer With SelectionnNew MacVim Buffer HerenThe latter Service now works in Finder on Snow Leopard (it was brokennbefore).  The Service Open Selected File has been deprecated since itndoes not seem very useful and it is rather confusing as to what itnreally does.n

Pass arguments to Vim on command lineDo not pass arguments via DO since some options only work if the filesnto open were passed on the command line (e.g. % flag in 'viminfo').nAlso, if a file is encrypted and opened from Spotlight the Spotlightnsearch text is passed as input and it ends up being used as password fornthe encryption key, so the file opens up encrypted.nnThe above problems still persist if Quickstart is enabled.n

Do not open files in unused windowsA window is unused if it has just been opened with Cmd+n.  Previouslyna file opened from Finder would be opened in an unused window if one wasnavailable.  This leads to problems with some Vim options, e.g. trying tonopen an encrypted file from Spotlight will fail.  The code that has beennremoved also had some quite ugly hacks and it is not entirely clearnwhether the reuse of unused windows was entirely intuitive.nn(The Open files from applications option is not affected by thisnchange.)n
Set cwd before launching Vim processThis fixes a bug where the 'exrc' option did not work when opening filesnfrom Finder.n
updated for version 7.2.360 Problem:Ruby on MS-Windows: can't use sockets. Solution:   Call NtInitialize() during initialization. (Ariya Mizutani)
updated for version 7.2.361 Problem:Ruby 1.9 is not supported. Solution:   Add Ruby 1.9 support. (Msaki Suketa)

updated for version 7.2.362 Problem:Win64: Vim doesn't work when cross-compiled with MingW libraries. Solution:   Instead of handling WM_NCCREATE, create wide text area window tclass if the parent window iw side. (Sergey Khorev)

updated for version 7.2.364 Problem:Can't build gvimext.dll on Win 7 x64 using MinGW (John Marriott) Solution:   Check if _MSC_VER is defined. (Andy Kittner)
updated for version 7.2.365 Problem:MS-Windows with MingW: File->Save As does not work. (John tMarriott) Solution:   Correctly fill in structure size. (Andy Kittner)
updated for version 7.2.366 Problem:CTRL-B doesn't go back to the first line of the buffer. Solution:   Avoid an overflow when adding MAXCOL.
updated for version 7.2.367 Problem:xxd -r -p doesn't work as documented. Solution:   Skip white space. (James Vega)
updated for version 7.2.368 Problem:Ruby interface: Appending line doesn't work. (Michael Henry) Solution:   Reverse check for NULL line. (James Vega)
Output build results in $(PROJECT_DIR)/buildThis overrides the global Xcode preference, which if set to a customizednlocation caused the build to fail.  (Patch by wezm)n
Add support for :winposNote that window coordinates are specified in a coordinate system wherenX points to the right and Y points upwards.n
updated for version 7.2.369 Problem:Error message is not easy to understand. Solution:   Add quotes. (SungHyun Nam)
updated for version 7.2.370 Problem:A redraw may cause folds to be closed. Solution:   Revert part of the previous patch.  Add a test. (Lech Lorens)
updated for version 7.2.371 Problem:Build problems on Tandem NonStop. Solution:   A few changes to #ifdefs (Joachim Schmitz)
updated for version 7.2.372 Problem:Cross-compiling GvimExt and xxd doesn't work. Solution:   Change the build files. (Markus Heidelberg)
updated for version 7.2.373 Problem:Gcc 4.5 adds more error messages. (Chris Indy) Solution:   Update default 'errorformat'.
updated for version 7.2.374 Problem:Ruby eval() doesn't understand Vim types. Solution:   Add the vim_to_ruby() function.  (George Gensure)
updated for version 7.2.375 Problem:ml_get errors when using :bprevious in a BufEnter autocmd. t(Dominique Pelle) Solution:   Clear w_valid when entering another buffer.
updated for version 7.2.376 Problem:ml_get error when using SiSU syntax. (Nathan Thomas) Solution:   If the match ends below the last line move it to the end of the tlast line.

updated for version 7.2.377 Problem:Misplaced assignment.  Duplicate build line for gvimext.dll. Solution:   Move setting CROSS_COMPILE to before ifneq.  Remove the wrong tbuild line. (Markus Heidelberg)
updated for version 7.2.378 Problem:C function declaration indented too much. (Rui) Solution:   Don't see a line containing { or } as a type. (Matt Wozniski)
updated for version 7.2.379 Problem:'eventignore' is set to an invalid value inside :doau. (Antony tScriven) Solution:   Don't include the leading comma when the option was empty.
updated for version 7.2.380 Problem:Perl interface builds with 5.10.1 but not with 5.10.0. Solution:   Change the #ifdefs. (Sergey Khorev)
updated for version 7.2.381 Problem:No completion for :behave. Solution:   Add :behave completion.  Minor related fixes. (Dominique Pelle)

updated for version 7.2.382 Problem:Accessing freed memory when closing the cmdline window when t'bufhide' is set to wipe. Solution:   Check if the buffer still exists before invoking close_buffer() t(Dominique Pelle)
updated for version 7.2.383 Problem:Vim doesn't build cleanly with MSVC 2010. Solution:   Change a few types. (George Reilly)
updated for version 7.2.384 Problem:Vim doesn't build properly with MSVC 2010. Solution:   Add the nmake version to the build file. (George Reilly)
updated for version 7.2.385 Problem:When in the command line window dragging status line only works tfor last-but-one window. (Jean Johner) Solution:   Remove the code that disallows this.
updated for version 7.2.386 Problem:Focus hack for KDE 3.1 causes problems for other window managers. Solution:   Remove the hack. (forwarded by Joel Bradshaw)
updated for version 7.2.387 Problem:Ruby with MingW still doesn't build all versions. Solution:   More #ifdefs for the  Ruby code. (Sergey Khorev)
updated for version 7.2.388 Problem:Ruby with MingW still doesn't build all versions. Solution:   Different approach to build file. (Sergey Khorev)
updated for version 7.2.389 Problem:synIDattr() cannot return the font. Solution:   Support the font argument. (Christian Brabandt)
updated for version 7.2.390 Problem:In some situations the popup menu can be displayed wrong. Solution:   Remove the popup menu if the cursor moved. (Lech Lorens)
updated for version 7.2.391 Problem:Internal alloc(0) error when doing CTRL-V $ c. (Martti Kuparinen) Solution:   Fix computations in getvcol(). (partly by Lech Lorens)
updated for version 7.2.392 Problem:Netbeans hangs reading from a socket at the maximum block size. Solution:   Use select() or poll(). (Xavier de Gaye)
updated for version 7.2.393 Problem:Mac: Can't build with different Xcode developer tools directory. Solution:   make Developer directory name configurable. (Rainer Muller)
updated for version 7.2.394 Problem:.xz files are not supported. Solution:   Recognize .xz files so that they can be edited.
updated for version 7.2.395 Problem:In help CTRL=] on g?g? escapes the ?, causing it to fail. (Tony tMechelynck) Solution:   Don't escape ? for a help command. (Sergey Khorev)

updated for version 7.2.397 Problem:Redundant check for w_lines_valid. Solution:   Remove the if.  (Lech Lorens)
updated for version 7.2.398 Problem:When moving windows the cursor ends up in the wrong line. Solution:   Set the window width and height properly. (Lech Lorens)
updated for version 7.2.399 Problem:Cannot compile on MingW Solution:   Move ifneq to separate line. (Vlad Sandrini, Dominique Pelle)

updated for version 7.2.400 Problem:Dynamic Ruby is not initialised properly for version 1.9.1. tRuby cannot create strings from NULL. Solution:   Cleanup #ifdefs.  Handle NULL like an empty string.  Add truby_init_stack. (Sergey Khorev)

updated for version 7.2.401 Problem::e dir<Tab> with 'wildmode' set to list doesn't highlight tdirectory names with a space. (Alexandre Provencio) Solution:   Remove the backslash before checking if the name is a directory. t(Dominique Pelle)

updated for version 7.2.405 Problem:When built with small features the matching text is not thighlighted for :s/pat/repl/c. Solution:   Remove the #ifdef for IncSearch. (James Vega)

updated for version 7.2.407 Problem:When using an expression in :s backslashes in the result are tdropped. (Sergey Goldgaber, Christian Brabandt) Solution:   Double backslashes.

updated for version 7.2.409 Problem:Summary of number of substitutes is incorrect for :folddo. (Jean tJohner) Solution:   Reset sub_nsubs and sub_nlines in global_exe().

updated for version 7.2.411 Problem:When parsing 'cino' a comma isn't skipped properly. Solution:   Skip the comma. (Lech Lorens)
updated for version 7.2.412 Problem:[ or ] followed by mouse click doesn't work. Solution:   Reverse check for key being a mouse event. (Dominique Pelle)
updated for version 7.2.413 Problem:Large file support is incorrect. Solution:   Add AC_SYS_LARGEFILE to configure. (James Vega)

updated for version 7.2.414 Problem:CTRK-K <space> <space> does not produce 0xa0 as expected. (Tony tMechelynck) Solution:   Remove the Unicode range 0xe000 - 0xefff from digraphs, these are tnot valid characters.

updated for version 7.2.416 Problem:Logtalk.dict is not installed. Solution:   Add it to the install target. (Markus Heidelberg)

updated for version 7.2.417 Problem:When 'shell' has an argument with a slash then 'shellpipe' is not tset properly. (Britton Kerin) Solution:   Assume there are no spaces in the path, arguments follow.

updated for version 7.2.418 Problem:Vim tries to set the background or foreground color in a terminal tto -1.  (Graywh)  Happens with :hi Normal ctermbg=NONE. Solution:   When resetting the foreground or background color don't set the tcolor, let the clear screen code do that.
updated for version 7.2.419 Problem:Memory leak in Motif when clicking on Search Vim Help. Solution:   Free string returned by XmTextGetString(). (Dominique Pelle)
updated for version 7.2.420 Problem::argedit does not accept ++enc=utf8 as documented. (Dominique tPelle) Solution:   Add the ARGOPT flag to :argedit.
updated for version 7.2.421 Problem:Folds are sometimes not updated properly and there is no way to tforce an update. Solution:   Make zx and zX recompute folds (suggested by Christian tBrabandt)
updated for version 7.2.422 Problem:May get E763 when using spell dictionaries. Solution:   Avoid utf-8 case folded character to be truncated to 8 bits and tdiffer from latin1. (Dominique Pelle)

updated for version 7.2.423 Problem:Crash when assigning s: to variable. (Yukihiro Nakadaira) Solution:   Make ga_scripts contain pointer to scriptvar_T instead of tscriptvar_T itself. (Dominique Pelle)
updated for version 7.2.424 Problem::colorscheme without an argument doesn't do anything. Solution:   Make it echo the current color scheme name.  (partly by Christian tBrabandt)
updated for version 7.2.425 Problem:Some compilers complain about fourth EX() argument. Solution:   Add cast to long_u.
updated for version 7.2.426 Problem:Commas in 'langmap' are not always handled correctly. Solution:   Require commas to be backslash escaped. (James Vega)
updated for version 7.2.427 Problem:The swapfile is created using the destination of a symlink, but trecovery doesn't follow symlinks. Solution:   When recovering, resolve symlinks. (James Vega)
updated for version 7.2.428 Problem:Using setqflist([]) to clear the error list doesn't work properly. Solution:   Set qf_nonevalid to TRUE when appropriate. (Christian Brabandt)

updated for version 7.2.429 Problem:A file that exists but access is denied may result in a new file tmessage.  E.g. when its directory is unreadable. Solution:   Specifically check for ENOENT to decide a file doesn't exist. t(partly by James Vega)

updated for version 7.2.430 Problem:The ++bad argument is handled wrong, resulting in an invalid tmemory access. Solution:   Use the bad_char field only for the replacement character, add tbad_char_idx to store the position. (Dominique Pelle)
updated for version 7.2.431 Problem::amenu moves the cursor when in Insert mode. Solution:   Use CTRL- CTRL-O instead of CTRL-O. (Christian Brabandt)

updated for version 7.2.432 Problem:When menus are translated they can only be found by the translated tname.  That makes :emenu difficult to use. Solution:   Store the untranslated name and use it for completion and :emenu. t(Edward L. Fox / Liang Peng / Bezetek James)
updated for version 7.2.433 Problem:Can't use cscope with QuickFixCmdPre and QuickFixCmdPost. Solution:   Add cscope support for these autocmd events. (Bryan Venteicher)

Double fork to avoid Vim hanging when using zsh
Revert Double fork to avoid Vim hanging when using zshThis reverts commit 453876f2672fa90691b9c541f9c12d7eea7e63b1.nnThis is not the right/complete solution.n

Fix Vim hanging when using zsh+gitThis fixes the problem explained in [2]. Essentially, when executingnexternal program, where default shell is zsh, Vim would hang. Thisnbehaviour does not occur with bash, or other shells.nnProblem:nWhen Vim executes an external program from GUI (MacVim in this case), itnopens PTYs. Parent passes information to the child via these PTYs. Savvynimplementation closes all unused filehandles, so slave PTY fd is closednin the parent immediately after fork(). This causes problems onnMacVim, due to [1]. In a nutshell, on BSD-like systems, write operationsnon PTY would block until one side reads or exits. If a child tries tonwrite on a PTY, which is closed in parent, that would block the child,nand stop further progress.nnResolution:nInstead of closing child's fd in the parent immediately after fork(),nclose it after child exits.nn[1] http://osdir.com/ml/darwin-kernel/2010-04/msg00025.htmln[2] http://groups.google.com/group/vim_mac/browse_thread/thread/78b18ce8cc15557dn

Improvements to Spotlight integrationNo longer issue a warning if the text entered in Spotlight can not benfound in a file opened from Spotlight.  Sanitize Spotlight input beforenpassing it on to Vim.n

Add support for trackpad gesturesSupported gestures are swipe, pinch and rotate.  These generate thenfollowing keys:nn<SwipeLeft> <SwipeRight> <SwipeUp> <SwipeDown>n<PinchIn>   <PinchOut>n<RotateCW>  <RotateCCW>nn(CW = ClockWise, CCW = CounterClockWise)n
Avoid <SwipeLeft> etc. being insertedPerforming a gesture will not cause <SwipeLeft> etc. to be inserted intonthe text while in insert mode/cmdline mode/etc.n
Use swipe gesture to navigate helpLeft/right swipe goes back/forward through tag stag when reading help.n

Deprecate Pinch/Rotate gesturesThese do not make much sense to include (and they could not easily benmapped to because of the fact that they generate events as the gesturenis being performed).nnAlso, make some updates to the help.n

Fix proxy icon response to modified buffersThe proxy icon is only disabled when the current buffer is modifiedn(previously this happened when any buffer was modified).  This also hasnthe consequence that the dot in the red close button only appears whennthe current buffer is modified.n

Avoid unnecessary clearing of the status lineWhen resizing a (Vim-) window don't use the CLEAR flag as it causes thenstatus line to be redrawn (which causes problems for plugins likenCommand-T).nnThe reason CLEAR was used in the first place was because resizing anwindow would cause display corruption due to wide letters like wnspilling over into the neigboring display cell.  To circumvent thisnproblem we now always clear neigboring blank cells whenever a cell isncleared (just like other GUIs deal with faked bold glyphs spilling overninto neighboring display cells).n

Add full screen window title to Window menu

Fix file open problem in full screen with SpacesThis fixes a problem when a full screen window was on another Space andnfiles were set to open in the topmost window.  Previously, this caused annew window to open on the current Space instead of opening the file innthe full screen window on the other Space.n

Avoid switching Spaces when entering full screenThis fixes a bug where MacVim would switch Space when entering fullnscreen (which only occurred when MacVim was assigned to a specificnSpace in the System Preferences).n
Fix compilation problems on OS X 10.4

Handle resolution changes while in full screenIf the screen resolution changes (either due to an external monitornbeing unplugged or because the settings were changed manually) the fullnscreen window is now resized to match the new resolution.  Before thisncommit full screen was exited on such an event.nnThis fixes a bug where the full screen option got out of sync after thenresolution changed.n
updated for version 7.3.095 Problem:Win32: In Chinese tear-off menu doesn't work. (Weasley) Solution:   Use menu_name_equal().  (Alex Jakushev)
updated for version 7.3.096 Problem:gvim -nb is not interruptable.  Leaking file descriptor on tnetbeans connection error. Solution:   Check for CTRL-C typed.  Free file descriptor.  (Xavier de Gaye)

updated for version 7.3.097 Problem:Using :call inside if 0 does not see that a function returns a tDict and gives error for . as string concatenation. Solution:   Use eval0() to skip over the expression.  (Yasuhiro Matsumoto)

updated for version 7.3.098 Problem:Function that ignores error still causes called_emsg to be set. tE.g. when expand() fails the status line is disabled. Solution:   Move check for emsg_not_now() up. (James Vega)
updated for version 7.3.099 Problem:Crash when splitting a window with zero height. (Yukihiro tNakadaira) Solution:   Don't set the fraction in a window with zero height.
Fix for dragging full screen window in SpacesEnsure the full screen window is still covering the screen after havingndragged it in Spaces (or moved it in any other manner).n
Avoid switching Spaces when leaving full screenThis fixes a bug where if the full screen window was moved to anothernSpace a Space switch would occur when leaving full screen.n
No partially grey window when leaving full screen
Hide Dock before entering full screenThis avoids the hide animation from playing after fading to black whennentering full screen.n

Add suppression tick box to termination alertThis will disable the warning about multiple window and tabs.  Tigernusers can access this functionality by setting the user defaultnMMSuppressTerminationAlert to 1.n

Fix open from Xcode with selection rangeThis is an initial attempt to fix a problem where double clicking ansearch result in Xcode would select an incorrect range of charactersnwhen the file opened in MacVim.  It only works the file uses an 8 bitnencoding.n
Fix untitled window opening regressionThis fixes a regression that caused two windows to open when a file wasnopened from Xcode (one window holding the file, the other empty).n
updated for version 7.3.100 Problem:When using :normal v:count isn't set. Solution:   Call normal_cmd() with toplevel set to TRUE.
updated for version 7.3.101 Problem:ino_t defined with wrong size. Solution:   Move including auto/config.h before other includes. (Marius tGeminas)

updated for version 7.3.102 Problem:When using :make, typing the next command and then getting the treload prompt the next command is (partly) eaten by the reload tprompt. Solution:   Accept ':' as a special character at the reload prompt to accept tthe default choice and execute the command.

Change heuristic to determine cell widthSome fonts (e.g. Monaco:h9) looked way too tight with the old heuristicnand the Core Text renderer.  Now the Core Text renderer uses the samenheuristic as the default renderer.n

Raise correct window on file openThis fixes a regression introduced in commit 210a71b4cb wherendouble-clicking a file in Finder that was already open would not causenthe window/tab containing that file to be raised.n

Add files opened from command line to MRUOnly files opened from the command line is added to the MRU (MostnRecently Used files).  Files opened from inside Vim (using :e, etc.) arennot added to the MRU.n

Add --nomru switchUse this switch from the command line to skip adding file to MRU listn(Most Recently Used files).  This may be useful when setting e.g.n$EDITOR to avoid temporary files from being added to the MRU.n

Fix compilation warnings in PSMTabBarControlThis also disables icon drawing code in tabs.  The reason being that thencode is unused, caused warnings and looked generally dangerous.n

Emergency fix for Ruby problemsWith optimizations enabled alloca(len) generates code which depends onnlen > 0.  If len == 0 then the stack pointer becomes botched.  Thisnfix simply avoids a call to alloca(len) in the latter case.  The rootnof this problem may be deeper than this, hence I am calling this annemergency fix for now but at least it fixes the crashes in the Rubyninterface that appear when compiling on Mac OS X 10.7.n
Addendum to emergency fixEnsure vim_message() outputs an empty message when the Ruby string hasnlength 0.  Failing to do this will cause the message area not to clearnwhen it should.n

Fix for zsh causing freezes on LionMake sure tty is opened using the same flags as when opening the pty.nIn particular, the O_NOCTTY was missing from the tty open call.  Thisncaused waitpid() to always return 0 and Vim would get stuck in annendless loop waiting for the child to exit.n

Emergency fix for Ruby problemsWith optimizations enabled alloca(len) generates code which depends onnlen > 0.  If len == 0 then the stack pointer becomes botched.  Thisnfix simply avoids a call to alloca(len) in the latter case.  The rootnof this problem may be deeper than this, hence I am calling this annemergency fix for now but at least it fixes the crashes in the Rubyninterface that appear when compiling on Mac OS X 10.7.n
Addendum to emergency fixEnsure vim_message() outputs an empty message when the Ruby string hasnlength 0.  Failing to do this will cause the message area not to clearnwhen it should.n

Fix for zsh causing freezes on LionMake sure tty is opened using the same flags as when opening the pty.nIn particular, the O_NOCTTY was missing from the tty open call.  Thisncaused waitpid() to always return 0 and Vim would get stuck in annendless loop waiting for the child to exit.n
Clicking full screen button updates 'fu' optionThis fixes a bug where the 'fu' option would not be updated when clickingnthe full screen button in the top right corner of a window.n
Switch spaces when closing window in full screenA remaining problem is that if there is another window open then it doesnnot get focus when the full screen window closes.n
Set proper animation behavior for windowThis causes a window to animate when it opens just like windows in othernLion apps do.n

Keep full screen window centered, change animationKeep the window centered in full screen when it changes size.  At thenmoment the Lion full screen background is shown around the window,nmeaning that the background option of 'fuopt' is ignored.nnThe animation when entering full screen is now a fade out of thendecorated window, followed by a fade in of the full screen window.  Anynattempts at making an animation of the window frame failed because ofnthe way content is drawn (by pushing drawing updates).  For this reasonnI settled on a fade animation which is not exactly pretty, but at leastnit is as objectionable as the default animation.nnA side effect of implementing a custom animation is that the correctnwindow now gets focus when closing a full screen window.n

Fix visibility of toolbar in full screenThe toolbar will pop up when the mouse is moved to the top of the screennin full screen mode if and only if it is visible outside of full screennmode.nnBug: if the toolbar is toggled in full screen mode then sometimes it isnno longer possible to enable it after exiting full screen.n
Change toolbar style in full screen
Map delete key to delete visual selectionAlso update the help.  The delete key used to be hard coded in thensource but now it is mapped in MacVim's gvimrc file instead.n
Support set fu in gvimrc for Lion full screen

Maximize both directions in full screen by defaultThe default for 'fuopt' is now maxhorz,maxvert.  Update help tonreflect this and add note that the background option of 'fuopt' is notnsupported when using Mac OS X native full screen mode.n
Fix for opening new window while in full screen
Handle screen parameter changes in full screen

Add user default for native/custom full screenThe boolean user default MMNativeFullScreen can be used to controlnwhether to use native or custom full-screen.  Set to 0 for custom, setnto 1 for native full-screen, for examplenn$ defaults write org.vim.MacVim MMNativeFullScreen 0nnThe default is to use native full-screen when available.  This userndefault does nothing on pre-Lion Mac OS X.nnAlso conditionally call Lion APIs so that it is possible to compile withn10.7 SDK but still support 10.6 (nb. 10.5 and earlier SDKs are notnsupported as of Xcode 4).  (Suggestion and initial patch by @splhack.)n

Force autorelease pool flush after an FSEventThe top-level autorelease pool only gets cleared out on applicationnevents, not including things like the FSEvent handler.  If MacVim is innthe background while ~/.vim changes, autoreleased objects will carry onnbuilding up until the users switches back to it, resulting in a highnmemory water mark and a lot of needless deallocs. Fix clang compiler and static analyzer warnings
Fix static analyzer warning in DBPrefs
Fix warnings etc in PSMTabBarControl frameworkThis also gets rid of a runtime warning that would get logged on OS Xn10.8 regarding the use of a deprecated method.n

Default to using CoreText rendererThe default renderer is too loose on OS X 10.8 whereas the CoreTextnrenderer looks the same across all platforms.  Furthermore, the CoreTextnrenderer is many times faster.nnA downside to the CoreText renderer is that it does not support the textninput protocols properly, so e.g. three-finger tapping to showndictionary results does not work.  It also does not show marked text asnit is being drawn if the inline marked text option is disabled.n
Disable toolbar by defaultThe toolbar is an anachronism and there are no 2x icons so it looksnhorrendous on a Retina display.  Users can always re-enable it by addingnset go+=T to their ~/.gvimrc.n
Rephrase text in advanced preferences dialog

Use u00e2u0080u009cinoremapu00e2u0080u009d for <M-BS> and <D-BS>As a Mac user Iu00e2u0080u0099m used to using Option-Delete to delete to the beginning of the previous word; MacVim sets up this behavior with its gvimrc.
